===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} or {{Han compound|白|水|t1=spring mouth|t2=water|ls=ic|nocap=y}} – water flowing from the source of a spring. See also [[原]].

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructs the Old Chinese as ''*dzwan'' and also reconstructs {{cog|tbq-pro|*tso||to bubble; to boil}} (> {{cog|bo|འཚོད་པ||to be boiled}}, {{cog|bo|བཙོས||to cook in boiling water}}, {{cog|my|ဆူ||to boil; to bubble}}), and considers {{och-l|泉|spring (of water)}} to be cognate to it (with an n-suffix nominalization). However, STEDT considers the above three Tibeto-Burman terms to be descended from {{cog|tbq-pro|*tsjow||to boil; to burn; to bake; to bake}}, to which {{och-l|焦|to roast; to burn; to scorch}} is cognate.

